      "writtenOn": "2016-04-19T07:33:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason setLooper() doesn\u0027t destroy the |looper| parameter on exit is because whoever created the looper is responsible for deleting it, which provides better control over destruction order. The instances created by Looper::get() on demand are definitely destroyed on thread exit.\n\nAlso, EmuGL doesn\u0027t use any Looper instances as far as I know (not surprisingly since it doesn\u0027t need to and doesn\u0027t include anything from android/base/ yet).\n\nIt looks like the only meaningful use case for this is in qemu-android/utils/qemu-thread-*.c, where we could just destroy the Looper instance after the thread returns instead.\n\nThe Qt and main QEMU threads are supposed to run until the end of the process, so I\u0027m not too concerned about them.",
      "parentUuid": "4881acc7_e5a3c0c3",
      "range": {
